<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="NAME"
>NAME <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Dist::Zilla - distribution builder; installer not included!</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="VERSION"
>VERSION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>version 4.300015</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="DESCRIPTION"
>DESCRIPTION <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>Dist::Zilla builds distributions of code to be uploaded to the CPAN.
In this respect,
it is like <a href="/perldoc?ExtUtils%3A%3AMakeMaker" class="podlinkpod"
>ExtUtils::MakeMaker</a>,
<a href="/perldoc?Module%3A%3ABuild" class="podlinkpod"
>Module::Build</a>,
or <a href="/perldoc?Module%3A%3AInstall" class="podlinkpod"
>Module::Install</a>.
Unlike those tools,
however,
it is not also a system for installing code that has been downloaded from the CPAN.
Since it&#39;s only run by authors,
and is meant to be run on a repository checkout rather than on published,
released code,
it can do much more than those tools,
and is free to make much more ludicrous demands in terms of prerequisites.</p>

<p>If you have access to the web,
you can learn more and find an interactive tutorial at <b><a href="http://dzil.org/" class="podlinkurl"
>dzil.org</a></b>.
If not,
try <a href="/~rjbs/Dist-Zilla-4.300015/lib/Dist/Zilla/Tutorial.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Dist::Zilla::Tutorial</a>.</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="ATTRIBUTES"
>ATTRIBUTES <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="name"
>name</a></h2>

<p>The name attribute (which is required) gives the name of the distribution to be built.
This is usually the name of the distribution&#39;s main module,
with the double colons (<code>::</code>) replaced with dashes.
For example: <code>Dist-Zilla</code>.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="version"
>version</a></h2>

<p>This is the version of the distribution to be created.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="abstract"
>abstract</a></h2>

<p>This is a one-line summary of the distribution.
If none is given,
one will be looked for in the <a href="#main_module" class="podlinkpod"
>&#34;main_module&#34;</a> of the dist.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="main_module"
>main_module</a></h2>

<p>This is the module where Dist::Zilla might look for various defaults,
like the distribution abstract.
By default,
it&#39;s derived from the distribution name.
If your distribution is Foo-Bar,
and <em>lib/Foo/Bar.pm</em> exists,
that&#39;s the main_module.
Otherwise,
it&#39;s the shortest-named module in the distribution.
This may change!</p>

<p>You can override the default by specifying the file path explicitly,
ie:</p>

<pre class="sh_perl">  main_module = lib/Foo/Bar.pm</pre>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="license"
>license</a></h2>

<p>This is the <a href="/perldoc?Software%3A%3ALicense" class="podlinkpod"
>Software::License</a> object for this dist&#39;s license and copyright.</p>

<p>It will be created automatically, if possible, with the <code>copyright_holder</code> and <code>copyright_year</code> attributes. If necessary, it will try to guess the license from the POD of the dist&#39;s main module.</p>

<p>A better option is to set the <code>license</code> name in the dist&#39;s config to something understandable, like <code>Perl_5</code>.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="authors"
>authors</a></h2>

<p>This is an arrayref of author strings, like this:</p>

<pre class="sh_perl">  [
    &#39;Ricardo Signes &#60;rjbs@cpan.org&#62;&#39;,
    &#39;X. Ample, Jr &#60;example@example.biz&#62;&#39;,
  ]</pre>

<p>This is likely to change at some point in the near future.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="files"
>files</a></h2>

<p>This is an arrayref of objects implementing <a href="/~rjbs/Dist-Zilla-4.300015/lib/Dist/Zilla/Role/File.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Dist::Zilla::Role::File</a> that will, if left in this arrayref, be built into the dist.</p>

<p>Non-core code should avoid altering this arrayref, but sometimes there is not other way to change the list of files. In the future, the representation used for storing files <b>will be changed</b>.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="root"
>root</a></h2>

<p>This is the root directory of the dist, as a <a href="/perldoc?Path%3A%3AClass%3A%3ADir" class="podlinkpod"
>Path::Class::Dir</a>. It will nearly always be the current working directory in which <code>dzil</code> was run.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="is_trial"
>is_trial</a></h2>

<p>This attribute tells us whether or not the dist will be a trial release.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="plugins"
>plugins</a></h2>

<p>This is an arrayref of plugins that have been plugged into this Dist::Zilla object.</p>

<p>Non-core code <b>must not</b> alter this arrayref. Public access to this attribute <b>may go away</b> in the future.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="distmeta"
>distmeta</a></h2>

<p>This is a hashref containing the metadata about this distribution that will be stored in META.yml or META.json. You should not alter the metadata in this hash; use a MetaProvider plugin instead.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="prereqs"
>prereqs</a></h2>

<p>This is a <a href="/~rjbs/Dist-Zilla-4.300015/lib/Dist/Zilla/Prereqs.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>Dist::Zilla::Prereqs</a> object, which is a thin layer atop <a href="/perldoc?CPAN%3A%3AMeta%3A%3APrereqs" class="podlinkpod"
>CPAN::Meta::Prereqs</a>, and describes the distribution&#39;s prerequisites.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="logger"
>logger</a></h2>

<p>This attribute stores a <a href="/perldoc?Log%3A%3ADispatchouli%3A%3AProxy" class="podlinkpod"
>Log::Dispatchouli::Proxy</a> object, used to log messages. By default, a proxy to the dist&#39;s <a href="/perldoc?Dist%3A%3AZilla%3A%3AChrome" class="podlinkpod"
>Chrome</a> is taken.</p>

<p>The following methods are delegated from the Dist::Zilla object to the logger:</p>

<ul>
<li>log</li>

<li>log_debug</li>

<li>log_fatal</li>
</ul>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="METHODS"
>METHODS <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="plugin_named"
>plugin_named</a></h2>

<pre class="sh_perl">  my $plugin = $zilla-&#62;plugin_named( $plugin_name );</pre>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="plugins_with"
>plugins_with</a></h2>

<pre class="sh_perl">  my $roles = $zilla-&#62;plugins_with( -SomeRole );</pre>

<p>This method returns an arrayref containing all the Dist::Zilla object&#39;s plugins that perform a the named role. If the given role name begins with a dash, the dash is replaced with &#34;Dist::Zilla::Role::&#34;</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="find_files"
>find_files</a></h2>

<pre class="sh_perl">  my $files = $zilla-&#62;find_files( $finder_name );</pre>

<p>This method will look for a <a href="/~rjbs/Dist-Zilla-4.300015/lib/Dist/Zilla/Role/FileFinder.pm" class="podlinkpod"
>FileFinder</a>-performing plugin with the given name and return the result of calling <code>find_files</code> on it. If no plugin can be found, an exception will be raised.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="stash_named"
>stash_named</a></h2>

<pre class="sh_perl">  my $stash = $zilla-&#62;stash_named( $name );</pre>

<p>This method will return the stash with the given name, or undef if none exists. It looks for a local stash (for this dist) first, then falls back to a global stash (from the user&#39;s global configuration).</p>

<h1><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="SUPPORT"
>SUPPORT <img alt='^' src='http://st.pimg.net/tucs/img/up.gif'></a></h1>

<p>There are usually people on <code>irc.perl.org</code> in <code>#distzilla</code>, even if they&#39;re idling.</p>

<p>The <a href="http://dzil.org/" class="podlinkurl"
>Dist::Zilla website</a> has several valuable resources for learning to use Dist::Zilla.</p>

<p>There is a mailing list to discuss Dist::Zilla. You can <a href="http://www.listbox.com/subscribe/?list_id=139292" class="podlinkurl"
>join the list</a> or <a href="http://listbox.com/member/archive/139292" class="podlinkurl"
>browse the archives</a>.</p>

